Italy coach Roberto Mancini  has reportedly called Gigio Donnarumma, while Juventus are once again interested in the PSG star. Donnarumma is in the spotlight after a costly error against Real Madrid in the second leg of the Champions League Round of 16 on Wednesday night. The 23-year-old sparked the Merengues’ comeback at the Bernabeu by losing the ball inside the box, leading to Karim Benzema’s equaliser.   Brilliant Benzema surpasses Di Stefano’s record     Manchester United’s Raphael Varane fit for Tottenham clash     Spectranet out with Stryker offer   According to La Gazzetta dello Sport newspaper, Italy coach Roberto Mancini called the 23-year-old yesterday to reassure him. The Azzurri will play the World Cup play-offs against North Macedonia in less than two weeks. The pink paper also reports that Juventus have resumed their interest in the ex-Milan goalkeeper who is considering his future in Paris. The 23-year-old has never really felt loved in the France capital and could consider his options at the end of the season.